PALPS. In general very similar to known congeners (cf. 
Figs 150–155
); coxa unmodified; trochanter with distinctive processes (
Fig. 165
); femur with indistinct small dorsal apophysis proximally; tibia very long (0.98); procursus with several distinctive elements (
Figs 167–168
); bulb with simple membranous embolus and strongly curved apophysis with rounded tip (
Fig. 166
).
